    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine mechanical and cosmetic form. This example is powered by the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M differential lock. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance: the VANOS system has been fully overhauled, rod bearings replaced with treated shells, and the rear subframe has been reinforced to ensure structural integrity. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping with fresh bushings, maintaining the sharp turn-in and neutral handling balance characteristic of the chassis. Free of any fluid seepage or diagnostic faults, this M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated German engineering.",
